<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-02-28T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-02-28T12:00:00-05:00" n="462" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d462">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/2275</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-02-28T17:00:00+00:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 28, 1916, 5 p. m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 7.20 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>3872. <persName corresp="#p_GSE1">Sir Edward Grey</persName> has
                                again informed me that he expects the English and French answer to
                                our long note on shipping to be <pb facs="0638" n="352" xml:id="pg_352"/> ready next week. The English answer is now
                                before the Cabinet and he is urging the French to haste. He
                                expresses regret at the long time consumed and wishes me to assure
                                you that he is hastening the answer as urgently as possible.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>